Google’s Android Beats Apple as Top Smartphone Operating System

-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 
2011-07-28T12:44:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/google-s-android-beats-apple-as-top-smartphone-operating-system.html
Google Inc. (GOOG) ’s Android operating
system was used on more smartphones in the U.S. last quarter
than  Apple Inc. (AAPL) ’s iOS, Nielsen Inc. said in a report today.  Android powered 39 percent of U.S. consumer smartphones in
the three months ended in June, compared with 28 percent for
Apple’s iOS. Waterloo, Ontario-based  Research in Motion Ltd. (RIM) ’s
BlackBerry operating system was used on 20 percent of
smartphones.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zachary Tracer in New York at 
 ztracer1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tom Giles at   tgiles@bloomberg.net . 